Function is a reusable block of code .
It can be call any where in the program
You can use the same code with different arguments to get the results.

JS:
Key word = function
()
Parameters=values(variables) 


 function greet(){
            console.log("hello nandu")
        }
        greet()
        console.log("hi nandhitha")
        greet()
        console.log("hi sai")

o/p:
hello nandu
 hi nandhitha
 hello nandu
 hi sai


 function g(name){
            console.log("hello "+ name)
        }
        let name=prompt("Enter your name?")
        g(name)

o/p:
Hello nandu

Funtion return :
The return statement can be used to return the value to function call.
Ex:
Function a(aa,bb){
Return aa+bb;
}
Let n1=parseFloat(prompt("enter the number1"))
Let n2=parseFloat(prompt("enter the number2"))
Let result =a(n1,n2);
Console.log("The sum is :"+result)

Anonynomus function : 
A function without any name , after we create a function without name and we assign it to a variable

Ex:
Sum=function(n1,n2){
Let r=n1+n2
Return r
}
Console.log(sum(8,9))
